Package: OpenClinica
Version: 3.18-SNAPSHOT
Title: OpenClinica Electronic Data Capture and Clinical Data Management System
Description: OpenClinica is an open source software for Electronic Data Capture (EDC)
    and Clinical Data Management (CDM) used to optimize clinical trial workflow in a
    smart and secure fashion. This installation is customized and maintained by
    Biostatech - Advice, Training & Innovation in Biostatistics, S.L.
Authors: OpenClinica Community, Biostatech (Customization)
License: GNU LGPL (https://www.openclinica.com/gnu-lgpl-open-source-license)
URL: https://github.com/OpenClinica/OpenClinica
BugReports: https://jira.openclinica.com/

SystemRequirements:
  Java: >= 7 (Java 7 or higher required)
  Maven: >= 3.0 (Maven 3.x required for building)
  Database: PostgreSQL 9.1+ or Oracle 10g+ (JDBC drivers included)
  Application Server: Apache Tomcat 6.x or compatible servlet container
  Memory: Minimum 2GB RAM recommended for production use
  Disk Space: Minimum 1GB for application, additional space for database

BuildRequirements:
  - Maven 3.x
  - Java Development Kit (JDK) 7 or higher
  - Access to OpenClinica artifact repository (openclinica.jfrog.io)
  - Access to JBoss public repository for some dependencies

RuntimeRequirements:
  - Java Runtime Environment (JRE) 7 or higher
  - Servlet container (Tomcat 6.x recommended)
  - PostgreSQL 9.1+ or Oracle 10g+ database
  - SMTP server for email notifications
  - Adequate disk space for audit trails and file attachments

